","description":"\"The Pilgrims boarded the Mayflower in search of religious freedom in the New World in September 1620. The Mayflower set sail from Plymouth, England, with 102 passengers, 40 of whom called themselves \"\"Saints.\"\" After two stormy months at sea, the ship reached the New World. Nearly half of the group died during their first winter due to malnutrition and the harsh New England winter.\"","url":"https://www.themayflowersociety.org/the-pilgrims/pilgrim-history","urlTitle":"The Mayflower Society - Pilgrim History","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705213,"age":22,"year":"1642","toYear":"1651","julianDay":2320789,"title":"The English Civil War","description":"A series of conflicts regarding England's governance during the years 1642 to 1651 is now known as The English Civil War. Charles I summoned supporters to join him against his enemies in Parliament. In October 1642, nearly 10,000 men fought for Charles I and chased Parliament across the River Tamar. Fighting continued for years and was finally ended at the Battle of Worcester on September 3, 1651, with a Parliamentarian victory.","jurisdictionLevel":1},{"id":1705216,"age":68,"year":"1688","toYear":"1689","julianDay":2337590,"title":"Glorious Revolution","description":"The Glorious Revolution brought the downfall of Catholic King James II and the reign of his Protestant daughter Mary and her Dutch husband, William III of Orange.","url":"http://www.bbc.co.uk/history/british/civil_war_revolution/glorious_revolution_01.shtml","urlTitle":"BBC - Glorious Revolution","jurisdictionLevel":1}],"lifeSummary":"Anne Foster was born in 1620, in Nottinghamshire, England. She had at least 1 daughter with Roger King. She died in November 1692, in Virginia, British Colonial America, at the age of 72."},"et":{"1620–November 1692":"1620–november 1692","1616–1653":"1616–1653","1650–1697":"1650–1697","1620–1692":"1620–1692","1689":"1689","1688":"1688","1620":"1620","1653":"1653","1642":"1642","1697":"1697","26 May 1650":